# This paper investigates the effectiveness of various valuation multiples, including Book-to-Price (B/P), Price-to-Earnings (P/E), Earnings Per Share (EPS), and Cash Earnings Per Share (CEPS), in capturing the value factor within the Nifty 500 universe over an extended time series. Additionally, it explores how strategic sector rotation and rebalancing can optimize the collection of risk premia through value and quality factors, offering insights into timing and sector-specific adjustments to enhance portfolio performance in the Indian equity market.

